00:05:58.790 --> 00:06:01.410
And over the course
of the last 10 years,

00:06:01.410 --> 00:06:05.060
I've noticed a big shift
in the central issues

00:06:05.060 --> 00:06:06.690
around parenting.

00:06:06.690 --> 00:06:12.010
And that shift is due mainly
to the more central role

00:06:12.010 --> 00:06:14.370
that technology is now
playing in the family.

00:06:14.370 --> 00:06:17.580
And I think this is one
of the big, big challenges

00:06:17.580 --> 00:06:20.810
that parents are
trying to work with.

00:06:20.810 --> 00:06:24.350
And the challenges that parents
face today in raising children

00:06:24.350 --> 00:06:28.140
are really, really different
than the challenges

00:06:28.140 --> 00:06:32.070
that their parents faced.

00:06:32.070 --> 00:06:34.040
Not only do parents
have to figure out

00:06:34.040 --> 00:06:36.850
how to do with less
sleep, but they also

00:06:36.850 --> 00:06:40.210
have to determine the role
they want technology to play

00:06:40.210 --> 00:06:42.470
in their child's development.

00:06:42.470 --> 00:06:45.220
If parents find
themselves with less time

00:06:45.220 --> 00:06:47.800
than they would like
to devote to parenting,

00:06:47.800 --> 00:06:50.830
they have to figure out new
strategies for discipline,

00:06:50.830 --> 00:06:53.870
nourishment, and enrichment.

00:06:53.870 --> 00:06:55.360
And this is
difficult when people

00:06:55.360 --> 00:06:59.280
find themselves trying
to navigate the issues

00:06:59.280 --> 00:07:02.240
around work/life balance.

00:07:02.240 --> 00:07:04.360
Many times people
have to face down

00:07:04.360 --> 00:07:08.470
issues of self-doubt
and guilt in trying

00:07:08.470 --> 00:07:10.600
to make the choices
that they want

00:07:10.600 --> 00:07:16.310
to make for the best and
highest good for their children.

00:07:16.310 --> 00:07:18.560
So one of the first
steps that parents

00:07:18.560 --> 00:07:22.050
must take toward
meeting these challenges

00:07:22.050 --> 00:07:25.040
and learning to parent
more consciously

00:07:25.040 --> 00:07:27.820
is to develop a
good understanding

00:07:27.820 --> 00:07:28.895
of their own values.

00:07:31.470 --> 00:07:33.860
If parents want to be
able to raise children

00:07:33.860 --> 00:07:36.490
who can meet the
challenges of the future

00:07:36.490 --> 00:07:40.180
with an open heart
and a focused mind,

00:07:40.180 --> 00:07:43.210
they must not only
understand, but be

00:07:43.210 --> 00:07:46.200
able to clearly
communicate their values

00:07:46.200 --> 00:07:50.130
to their children in everything
they do and in everything they

00:07:50.130 --> 00:07:52.240
say.

00:07:52.240 --> 00:07:56.060
So in order to be able to
communicate values clearly

00:07:56.060 --> 00:07:59.220
and to apply them
in a consistent way,

00:07:59.220 --> 00:08:04.680
parents must spend some time
learning what their values are.

00:08:04.680 --> 00:08:07.100
This may sound simple.

00:08:07.100 --> 00:08:10.620
But it's surprising to see
how many people struggle

00:08:10.620 --> 00:08:13.680
to articulate their
values for themselves,

00:08:13.680 --> 00:08:16.380
and much less for
their children.

00:08:16.380 --> 00:08:18.900
The effort to engage
in this articulation

00:08:18.900 --> 00:08:23.800
is very important, perhaps one
of the most important steps

00:08:23.800 --> 00:08:27.020
that parents must take
in order to parent

00:08:27.020 --> 00:08:31.400
with more mindfulness
and more awareness.

00:08:31.400 --> 00:08:34.909
Because parenting
is taking place now

00:08:34.909 --> 00:08:39.360
in such a different environment,
role models and mentors

00:08:39.360 --> 00:08:41.820
are difficult to come by.

00:08:41.820 --> 00:08:45.300
This compounds an
already age-old problem,

00:08:45.300 --> 00:08:49.700
which is that many of us were
parented by people who weren't

00:08:49.700 --> 00:08:51.790
parented well themselves.

00:08:51.790 --> 00:08:59.370
So we have this legacy of less
than ideal situations leading

00:08:59.370 --> 00:09:01.330
into parenting.

00:09:01.330 --> 00:09:05.460
So many parents just
don't have the role models

00:09:05.460 --> 00:09:08.130
they need readily
at hand when they're

00:09:08.130 --> 00:09:10.900
trying to make decisions
about screen time,

00:09:10.900 --> 00:09:15.100
toilet training,
internet privacy,

00:09:15.100 --> 00:09:19.030
curfews, it's all together.

00:09:19.030 --> 00:09:21.110
And it's important
therefore to seek

00:09:21.110 --> 00:09:24.340
role models who hold the
values that you hold,

00:09:24.340 --> 00:09:26.870
and seek their help.

00:09:26.870 --> 00:09:32.390
In order to do this, you have
to define your own values.

00:09:32.390 --> 00:09:33.820
What is important to you?

00:09:37.310 --> 00:09:39.305
Do you know how to
begin to answer this?

00:09:44.490 --> 00:09:47.230
Do you have a clear
idea of what values

00:09:47.230 --> 00:09:50.780
you want your children to
bring forward into the world

00:09:50.780 --> 00:09:54.410
as they mature and take
their place in confronting

00:09:54.410 --> 00:09:56.360
the complexities of
the modern world?

00:10:01.830 --> 00:10:07.220
Let's start at a fairly high
level here looking at values.

00:10:07.220 --> 00:10:08.920
So I'd like you to
just take a moment

00:10:08.920 --> 00:10:13.636
and focus inward
and allow yourself

00:10:13.636 --> 00:10:20.900
to consider two spiritual values
that are important to you.

00:10:20.900 --> 00:10:27.936
So just let yourself
think for a moment.

00:10:27.936 --> 00:10:31.560
What are two spiritual values
that are important to you?

00:10:44.810 --> 00:10:49.170
And if you're
co-parenting, what are

00:10:49.170 --> 00:10:52.610
two spiritual values you know to
be of value to your co-parent?

00:11:05.030 --> 00:11:09.620
If there are differences
in your sets of values,

00:11:09.620 --> 00:11:13.040
what is your strategy for
bridging those differences

00:11:13.040 --> 00:11:15.900
so you can present a unified
message to your children?

00:11:18.730 --> 00:11:22.040
If your values are
similar, what kinds

00:11:22.040 --> 00:11:24.160
of activities and
interactions do you

00:11:24.160 --> 00:11:27.822
create on a regular basis
to communicate those values

00:11:27.822 --> 00:11:28.530
to your children?

00:11:40.150 --> 00:11:42.550
Given the importance
of these values,

00:11:42.550 --> 00:11:46.090
whom do you have to turn
to, to help you continue

00:11:46.090 --> 00:11:49.307
to address and develop
these values in parenting

00:11:49.307 --> 00:11:49.890
your children?

00:11:57.510 --> 00:12:01.800
You can see how much goes into
the development of just one

00:12:01.800 --> 00:12:03.900
set of values.

00:12:03.900 --> 00:12:07.060
But there are many other
values to look at in order

00:12:07.060 --> 00:12:11.770
to be able to parent with as
much mindfulness, awareness,

00:12:11.770 --> 00:12:13.320
and consciousness as possible.

00:12:16.320 --> 00:12:21.950
As I was putting my thoughts
together to talk to you,

00:12:21.950 --> 00:12:25.490
I thought I was going to
touch more fully on the issues

00:12:25.490 --> 00:12:27.640
that we touch on in
the conscious parenting

00:12:27.640 --> 00:12:32.370
classes at the Sacred Stream
Center in Berkeley, California.

00:12:32.370 --> 00:12:37.690
These classes focus on helping
parents locate inner resources,

00:12:37.690 --> 00:12:41.000
and learning how to
draw upon them better.

00:12:41.000 --> 00:12:44.670
They focus on helping parents
articulate their needs

00:12:44.670 --> 00:12:47.070
and values.

00:12:47.070 --> 00:12:51.240
And they help parents learn
how to work effectively

00:12:51.240 --> 00:12:57.490
with willfulness, and focus on
discipline more effectively.

00:12:57.490 --> 00:13:00.060
And they offer
parents strategies

00:13:00.060 --> 00:13:02.120
for parenting a child
who is challenged.

00:13:04.860 --> 00:13:06.850
The reason for
examining these issues

00:13:06.850 --> 00:13:10.270
in the context of conscious
parenting is simple.

00:13:10.270 --> 00:13:14.980
When these issues are addressed,
the protection and cultivation

00:13:14.980 --> 00:13:18.680
of the child's authentic
expression in the world

00:13:18.680 --> 00:13:21.190
is assured.

00:13:21.190 --> 00:13:25.890
And if you were to ask me
to define one goal that we

00:13:25.890 --> 00:13:29.660
as parents must do
our best to attain,

00:13:29.660 --> 00:13:33.640
I would say that it is
this-- the protection

00:13:33.640 --> 00:13:37.390
and cultivation of our
child's authentic expression

00:13:37.390 --> 00:13:39.940
in the world.

00:13:39.940 --> 00:13:45.210
So that is the topic I would
like to focus on here today.

00:13:45.210 --> 00:13:47.120
Whenever I'm working
with families,

00:13:47.120 --> 00:13:50.480
especially the parents
of young children,

00:13:50.480 --> 00:13:55.620
I always try to walk a line
between creating a forum where

00:13:55.620 --> 00:13:59.410
people can understand
themselves more fully

00:13:59.410 --> 00:14:03.210
so that they can understand how
many resources they actually

00:14:03.210 --> 00:14:08.990
have, and offering advice
or council from that place,

00:14:08.990 --> 00:14:12.580
and the line between
offering opinion.

00:14:12.580 --> 00:14:17.650
It's really easy for me to go
into opinion about parenting.

00:14:17.650 --> 00:14:19.880
But I'm really going
to try not to do that.

00:14:19.880 --> 00:14:20.480
But I might.

00:14:20.480 --> 00:14:23.830
I might wander into
the opinion place,

00:14:23.830 --> 00:14:27.270
because this is really
so close to my heart--

00:14:27.270 --> 00:14:32.440
this idea of being able
to protect your child's

00:14:32.440 --> 00:14:33.730
expression in the world.

00:14:33.730 --> 00:14:35.220
This is so important.

00:14:37.920 --> 00:14:41.420
Many great educators,
including Maria Montessori

00:14:41.420 --> 00:14:44.900
and Rudolf Steiner,
spoke to this issue, each

00:14:44.900 --> 00:14:47.080
in their own way.

00:14:47.080 --> 00:14:49.990
They each offered structures
that support children

00:14:49.990 --> 00:14:51.840
and having the
freedom to discover

00:14:51.840 --> 00:14:56.420
their own unique talents,
gifts, and capacities.

00:14:56.420 --> 00:15:00.650
And they also offer structures
to address areas of weaknesses

00:15:00.650 --> 00:15:05.430
or obstacles that children may
have which affect their ability

00:15:05.430 --> 00:15:08.870
to fully move into the world
with those native gifts.

00:15:11.870 --> 00:15:16.420
The reason that the discussion
around values is so important

00:15:16.420 --> 00:15:20.750
is because it is values that
become the structures we

00:15:20.750 --> 00:15:23.610
offer our children
within which they

00:15:23.610 --> 00:15:25.365
learn to express themselves.

