the authentic expression

00:16:06.690 --> 00:16:12.100
of the child, children spend
important developmental time

00:16:12.100 --> 00:16:15.880
trying to adapt themselves
to values which have nothing

00:16:15.880 --> 00:16:18.870
to do with their
authentic expression,

00:16:18.870 --> 00:16:22.700
and which in fact may impede it.

00:16:22.700 --> 00:16:26.040
How many of you have spent
time trying to navigate around

00:16:26.040 --> 00:16:28.800
a parent with anger issues?

00:16:28.800 --> 00:16:29.940
Or addiction issues?

00:16:33.350 --> 00:16:36.860
What did that do to your
ability to know what calls

00:16:36.860 --> 00:16:38.415
to you from your own heart?

00:16:44.790 --> 00:16:47.370
It is, I believe,
important to consider

00:16:47.370 --> 00:16:50.170
that our most important
task as parents

00:16:50.170 --> 00:16:54.330
is to try to develop a family
system whose structures support

00:16:54.330 --> 00:16:56.770
the authentic expression
of the highest

00:16:56.770 --> 00:16:59.860
potential of our children,
to help them learn

00:16:59.860 --> 00:17:05.220
how to listen to what is calling
to them in their own hearts.

00:17:05.220 --> 00:17:06.510
This may sound easy.

00:17:06.510 --> 00:17:08.030
But it's not.

00:17:08.030 --> 00:17:11.319
When some people hear
this, they think, OK.

00:17:11.319 --> 00:17:13.480
Anything goes.

00:17:13.480 --> 00:17:15.079
Let the kids do
whatever they want.

00:17:15.079 --> 00:17:19.030
As long as they're expressing,
it's going to be OK.

00:17:19.030 --> 00:17:22.339
Or other parents may
hear this and think, OK.

00:17:22.339 --> 00:17:25.010
I have to figure out what my
child's highest potential is

00:17:25.010 --> 00:17:29.120
and steer that child
toward them at every turn.

00:17:29.120 --> 00:17:32.120
Other parents may
respond, they're my kids.

00:17:32.120 --> 00:17:34.390
They're going to do what I
want, not what they want.

00:17:36.970 --> 00:17:40.270
But the task at hand is
more nuanced than any

00:17:40.270 --> 00:17:42.720
of these approaches.

00:17:42.720 --> 00:17:45.140
First of all, we
need to define what

00:17:45.140 --> 00:17:48.950
we mean by a child's
highest potential, which

00:17:48.950 --> 00:17:52.500
I am using interchangeably
here with the child's deepest

00:17:52.500 --> 00:17:56.870
calling, the child's most
authentic expression,

00:17:56.870 --> 00:17:59.230
the child's gifts.

00:17:59.230 --> 00:18:01.750
I'm using these terms
interchangeably,

00:18:01.750 --> 00:18:06.320
because they each offer a
different view and definition

00:18:06.320 --> 00:18:09.830
that point to the
complexity of the deepest

00:18:09.830 --> 00:18:13.230
aspects of our children.

00:18:13.230 --> 00:18:15.800
Naturally, every child's
highest potential

00:18:15.800 --> 00:18:18.400
has its own expression.

00:18:18.400 --> 00:18:20.750
Every child has a
set of gifts that she

00:18:20.750 --> 00:18:24.040
brings into the world that
resonate with her highest

00:18:24.040 --> 00:18:25.820
calling.

00:18:25.820 --> 00:18:28.790
We must at once try
to tune ourselves

00:18:28.790 --> 00:18:31.980
to this deepest aspect
of our children,

00:18:31.980 --> 00:18:35.300
understand its
requirements, and get out

00:18:35.300 --> 00:18:38.780
of the way of impeding
its expression,

00:18:38.780 --> 00:18:44.850
while at the same time creating
structures which support it.

00:18:44.850 --> 00:18:47.380
This may sound like
rubbing your belly

00:18:47.380 --> 00:18:50.460
and tapping your head
at the same time.

00:18:50.460 --> 00:18:52.340
And indeed, it is.

00:18:52.340 --> 00:18:55.730
But it is something we
can learn how to do.

00:18:55.730 --> 00:18:59.250
So I would like to identify
some of these tasks that will

00:18:59.250 --> 00:19:01.320
help you with this process.

00:19:01.320 --> 00:19:03.590
First individually,
and then show you

00:19:03.590 --> 00:19:08.090
how to put them together so
that the tapping and the rubbing

00:19:08.090 --> 00:19:11.670
seems intuitive and easy.

00:19:11.670 --> 00:19:14.470
These tasks center
around a set of questions

00:19:14.470 --> 00:19:17.500
I would like to offer you.

00:19:17.500 --> 00:19:21.970
First, how do I recognize
my child's deepest calling?

00:19:26.800 --> 00:19:31.215
Two, how do I recognize
my child's gifts?

00:19:36.950 --> 00:19:41.520
Three, why do I have to get out
of the way of the expression

00:19:41.520 --> 00:19:42.520
of my child's potential?

00:19:45.810 --> 00:19:49.090
Four, how do I get
out of the way?

00:19:52.720 --> 00:19:56.040
Five, what does
it mean to create

00:19:56.040 --> 00:19:59.750
structures that support the
expression of my child's

00:19:59.750 --> 00:20:00.250
potential?

00:20:05.730 --> 00:20:09.370
So we're going to address each
one of these individually.

00:20:09.370 --> 00:20:13.610
The first question is, how do
I recognize my child's deepest

00:20:13.610 --> 00:20:16.160
calling?

00:20:16.160 --> 00:20:20.300
This is actually
surprisingly easy to do.

00:20:20.300 --> 00:20:22.340
It is really just a
matter of watching

00:20:22.340 --> 00:20:26.490
what your child is drawn to.

00:20:26.490 --> 00:20:31.180
Your children will naturally be
drawn to their highest calling

00:20:31.180 --> 00:20:32.903
if they are not interrupted.

00:20:38.160 --> 00:20:41.630
How do I recognize
my child's gifts?

00:20:41.630 --> 00:20:43.500
The answer is the same.

00:20:43.500 --> 00:20:46.650
Watch what your
child is drawn to.

00:20:46.650 --> 00:20:52.220
But recognizing the child's
gifts goes one step further.

00:20:52.220 --> 00:20:56.410
This involves watching what
games the child creates,

00:20:56.410 --> 00:21:01.380
what stories the child
tells, and the way the child

00:21:01.380 --> 00:21:02.720
seeks to express herself.

00:21:05.330 --> 00:21:08.830
There is an important part to
cultivating a child's gifts

00:21:08.830 --> 00:21:12.150
that has to do with the
filtering of the kind

00:21:12.150 --> 00:21:14.360
of information
that the child uses

00:21:14.360 --> 00:21:16.940
as raw material for
that expression.

00:21:16.940 --> 00:21:19.250
And I will speak to
that in just a moment.

00:21:22.510 --> 00:21:25.500
The next question
is, why do I have

00:21:25.500 --> 00:21:28.171
to get out of the way of
the expression of my child's

00:21:28.171 --> 00:21:28.670
potential?

00:21:32.610 --> 00:21:34.940
We tend to think of
our children as ours.

00:21:38.250 --> 00:21:40.245
But they actually
belong to themselves.

00:21:43.790 --> 00:21:46.290
If they are lucky, their
path through this life

00:21:46.290 --> 00:21:51.580
is a long one that extends
far beyond the few years

00:21:51.580 --> 00:21:52.730
that we care for them.

00:21:55.550 --> 00:22:00.920
It is important to consider that
your ideas about what you want

00:22:00.920 --> 00:22:06.580
for your child beyond wanting
them to be happy and safe

00:22:06.580 --> 00:22:09.320
might become interrupting
to their natural expression.

00:22:11.930 --> 00:22:14.840
How many of you wanted
to study music, but were

00:22:14.840 --> 00:22:17.590
told by your parents you had
to go to business school?

00:22:23.060 --> 00:22:26.200
What message did this give
you about the possibility

00:22:26.200 --> 00:22:29.790
of being supported in the
world by your deepest calling?

00:22:34.620 --> 00:22:37.360
How does this affect you
on a daily basis today?

00:22:43.330 --> 00:22:46.290
With this information,
consider how important

00:22:46.290 --> 00:22:49.510
it is to give your child the
message that he can trust

00:22:49.510 --> 00:22:53.230
his deepest calling, and that
he will be able to find a way

00:22:53.230 --> 00:22:56.200
to let that expression of
that calling-- whatever

00:22:56.200 --> 00:23:00.130
that expression
is-- support him.

00:23:00.130 --> 00:23:02.930
Give him practice in
letting all the potential

00:23:02.930 --> 00:23:05.400
that the calling
and that calling

00:23:05.400 --> 00:23:09.540
express itself by
supporting what he loves.

00:23:09.540 --> 00:23:10.900
And step out of the way.

00:23:14.040 --> 00:23:18.384
Next question is, how
do I get out of the way?

00:23:18.384 --> 00:23:20.870
Well, I've got a long
answer to this question.

00:23:20.870 --> 00:23:24.280
So bear with me.

00:23:24.280 --> 00:23:26.830
One of the best ways
to get out of the way

00:23:26.830 --> 00:23:29.670
is to look at your
attachments to your children

00:23:29.670 --> 00:23:33.220
being a particular way.

00:23:33.220 --> 00:23:36.410
Those attachments are probably
a function of something

00:23:36.410 --> 00:23:38.210
that did not work in
your own childhood.

00:23:41.580 --> 00:23:45.120
For instance, let's say
you grew up in a household

00:23:45.120 --> 00:23:47.660
without a mother present.

00:23:47.660 --> 00:23:51.640
And you felt her absence keenly.

00:23:51.640 --> 00:23:56.045
You grow, you marry a woman,
and you have children.

00:23:58.600 --> 00:24:01.310
And then you realize this
woman is more problematic

00:24:01.310 --> 00:24:03.050
than I thought.

00:24:03.050 --> 00:24:07.250
This is not the person I
thought I was marrying.

00:24:07.250 --> 00:24:09.500
But now you have children.

00:24:09.500 --> 00:24:11.510
And because you
know how hard it was

00:24:11.510 --> 00:24:14.090
for you not to
have a mother, you

00:24:14.090 --> 00:24:18.946
put up with all kinds of bad
behavior from your spouse

00:24:18.946 --> 00:24:22.780
or from the child's mother,
rather than take the child

00:24:22.780 --> 00:24:26.060
and leave the situation
and take the risk

00:24:26.060 --> 00:24:28.820
that the child may grow up
without a full-time mother

00:24:28.820 --> 00:24:30.790
figure.

00:24:30.790 --> 00:24:32.690
If you were not so
attached to your child

00:24:32.690 --> 00:24:35.090
having a mother
because of the pain

00:24:35.090 --> 00:24:38.560
that you experienced
at not having a mother,

00:24:38.560 --> 00:24:40.960
you might have more
clarity in responding

00:24:40.960 --> 00:24:44.140
to your spouse's bad behavior.

00:24:44.140 --> 00:24:45.300
Who knows?

00:24:45.300 --> 00:24:48.170
Not having this problematic
woman in your child's life

00:24:48.170 --> 00:24:51.020
on such a consistent
basis might be

00:24:51.020 --> 00:24:54.740
the best thing for your child.

00:24:54.740 --> 00:24:57.400
But you cannot see this,
or even consider it

00:24:57.400 --> 00:25:00.660
because of the unaddressed
issues that you carry from

00:25:00.660 --> 00:25:02.530
your own wounding
at being motherless.

00:25:07.290 --> 00:25:10.970
In many ways, when we talk
about conscious parenting,

00:25:10.970 --> 00:25:14.220
we are talking about becoming
more conscious of ourselves.

00:25:16.980 --> 00:25:19.140
We are talking
about understanding

00:25:19.140 --> 00:25:22.240
what motivates us before we
even approach our children.

00:25:24.810 --> 00:25:27.190
The examination
of our motivation

00:25:27.190 --> 00:25:29.830
and the way that it
drives decision-making

00:25:29.830 --> 00:25:32.240
is a good example
of one of the steps

00:25:32.240 --> 00:25:37.420
in the process of becoming
a more aware parent.

00:25:37.420 --> 00:25:41.050
Again, one of the best
ways to get out of the way

00:25:41.050 --> 00:25:44.800
is to stop risking
interrupting your child's

00:25:44.800 --> 00:25:48.610
authentic expression,
and to look deeply

00:25:48.610 --> 00:25:53.050
at your own experience
of being parented.

00:25:53.050 --> 00:25:56.390
Seek to understand the
aspects of your upbringing

00:25:56.390 --> 00:26:01.540
that worked best for you and
your own self-expression.

00:26:01.540 --> 00:26:05.100
And ask how you can apply
that understanding to serving

00:26:05.100 --> 00:26:08.080
your child's expression.

00:26:08.080 --> 00:26:11.360
In this way you can tap
into your own resources

00:26:11.360 --> 00:26:12.675
and become your own mentor.

00:26:15.660 --> 00:26:18.740
You can also look at the
aspects of your upbringing

00:26:18.740 --> 00:26:22.470
that did not work
for you, and get help

00:26:22.470 --> 00:26:25.830
in changing the way that these
aspects of your childhood

00:26:25.830 --> 00:26:26.770
affect you today.

00:26:31.170 --> 00:26:32.680
I remember when
I first found out

00:26:32.680 --> 00:26:35.070
I was pregnant with
my first child.

00:26:35.070 --> 00:26:37.626
I was looking at the
pregnancy indicator.

00:26:37.626 --> 00:26:38.750
And it was like it was yes.

00:26:38.750 --> 00:26:40.420
And I'm like, oh!

00:26:40.420 --> 00:26:43.530
And I literally with the
indicator still in my hand,

00:26:43.530 --> 00:26:44.700
I ran to the phone.

00:26:44.700 --> 00:26:46.440
We made phone calls back then.

00:26:46.440 --> 00:26:49.000
I ran to the phone and
I called a therapist.

00:26:49.000 --> 00:26:54.930
And I literally had the receiver
for the phone and the pregnancy

00:26:54.930 --> 00:26:58.300
kit indicator in
my hand, because I

00:26:58.300 --> 00:27:00.750
knew there was no
way I was going

00:27:00.750 --> 00:27:04.210
to be able to face the
challenges of mothering

00:27:04.210 --> 00:27:10.780
with all of my own
childhood experience

00:27:10.780 --> 00:27:14.450
affecting me in
an uninformed way.

00:27:14.450 --> 00:27:16.580
I mean, I didn't
know much back then.

00:27:16.580 --> 00:27:19.210
But I knew that, right?

00:27:19.210 --> 00:27:23.900
So not only do you have
to get out of the way

00:27:23.900 --> 00:27:27.580
by addressing your own
unexamined experience in order

00:27:27.580 --> 00:27:31.030
to be as clear as possible about
how to support your child's

00:27:31.030 --> 00:27:35.730
potential, but it is
also important to look

00:27:35.730 --> 00:27:39.950
at the experience that the child
is exposed to in the larger

00:27:39.950 --> 00:27:42.870
cultural context.

00:27:42.870 --> 00:27:45.670
With the newfound
clarity gained in looking

00:27:45.670 --> 00:27:48.890
at your personal issues,
you can determine

00:27:48.890 --> 00:27:52.420
if the experience of the
larger cultural environment

00:27:52.420 --> 00:27:55.380
is supporting your
child's potential or not.

00:27:57.930 --> 00:28:00.620
And this is where
that raw material

00:28:00.620 --> 00:28:04.740
the child uses to formulate
her expression that I just

00:28:04.740 --> 00:28:05.980
spoke about comes in.

00:28:08.560 --> 00:28:11.520
And it is also where
the issue of values

00:28:11.520 --> 00:28:17.460
comes into play in
a very powerful way.

00:28:17.460 --> 00:28:19.850
You have to understand
what you value

00:28:19.850 --> 00:28:24.590
and what you don't value in
the larger cultural context.

00:28:24.590 --> 00:28:27.310
How do you feel
about screen time

00:28:27.310 --> 00:28:28.485
versus personal engagement?

00:28:35.157 --> 00:28:36.740
Something to think
about for a minute.

00:28:42.910 --> 00:28:46.760
What role should technology play
in early childhood development?

00:28:57.490 --> 00:29:00.120
What level of violence
in computer games

00:29:00.120 --> 00:29:01.190
is acceptable to you?

00:29:09.750 --> 00:29:12.499
How do you feel about letting
children play with toy guns?

00:29:23.270 --> 00:29:25.930
The answer to these questions
will determine the answer

00:29:25.930 --> 00:29:28.810
to the last question for you.

00:29:28.810 --> 00:29:31.430
What does it mean
to create structures

00:29:31.430 --> 00:29:34.290
that support the expression
of my child's potential?

00:29:39.390 --> 00:29:41.820
The choices that you
make around values

00:29:41.820 --> 00:29:44.229
create the structures
that support

00:29:44.229 --> 00:29:45.270
your child's development.

00:29:47.900 --> 00:29:50.930
If you have no
defined value system,

00:29:50.930 --> 00:29:53.930
the values of the
larger cultural context

00:29:53.930 --> 00:29:58.350
will become the structure
that supports or impedes

00:29:58.350 --> 00:29:59.350
your child's expression.

00:30:02.440 --> 00:30:05.890
If your values are based
on an unexamined response

00:30:05.890 --> 00:30:08.420
to the way you
were parented, they

00:30:08.420 --> 00:30:11.660
will become the
structures that support

00:30:11.660 --> 00:30:15.630
or impede the expression of
your child's authentic self.

00:30:18.300 --> 00:30:19.920
Is this what you
want for your child?

00:30:27.016 --> 00:30:30.800
If the answer is no,
you already understand

00:30:30.800 --> 00:30:34.640
why conscious parenting
is so important.

00:30:34.640 --> 00:30:37.180
If you enter into
parenting without being

00:30:37.180 --> 00:30:39.250
aware of the values
that are driving

00:30:39.250 --> 00:30:41.740
your decisions
around parenting, you

00:30:41.740 --> 00:30:46.050
will not know how to define
or articulate your values.

00:30:46.050 --> 00:30:49.130
If you don't have clear values,
you cannot know how to create

00:30:49.130 --> 00:30:52.560
structures that support
you in skillfully guiding

00:30:52.560 --> 00:30:55.345
the manifestation of your
child's highest potential.

00:30:58.300 --> 00:31:01.970
So as you get ready to
practice rubbing your belly

00:31:01.970 --> 00:31:05.460
and tapping your
head at the same time

00:31:05.460 --> 00:31:09.340
as you step into becoming
a more conscious parent,

00:31:09.340 --> 00:31:13.790
just remember--
all you have to do

00:31:13.790 --> 00:31:19.220
is observe carefully what
your child is drawn to.

00:31:19.220 --> 00:31:20.780
What stories is he telling you?

00:31:23.750 --> 00:31:25.135
How does she express herself?

00:31:28.330 --> 00:31:31.260
Invest time in looking
at your own experience

00:31:31.260 --> 00:31:33.090
of being parented.

00:31:33.090 --> 00:31:35.475
And see what worked for
you and what did not.

00:31:39.320 --> 00:31:43.260
Take time to understand
the extent to which you

00:31:43.260 --> 00:31:46.680
want the larger cultural
context to participate

00:31:46.680 --> 00:31:47.990
in the formation of your child.

00:31:51.740 --> 00:31:53.830
If you follow these
steps, you will

00:31:53.830 --> 00:31:59.120
know how to create experiences
which provide enough structure

00:31:59.120 --> 00:32:02.070
to nurture your
child's potential,

00:32:02.070 --> 00:32:04.790
but not so much
structure that it

00:32:04.790 --> 00:32:08.190
stifles the expression
of your child's

00:32:08.190 --> 00:32:09.785
heart's deepest calling.

00:32:13.110 --> 00:32:13.610
See.

00:32:13.610 --> 00:32:15.315
No so hard.

00:32:15.315 --> 00:32:17.565
Conscious parenting may not
be as hard as you thought.

00:32:21.500 --> 00:32:25.780
In these times when we are
facing societal upheaval,

00:32:25.780 --> 00:32:29.610
environmental destruction,
and so much uncertainty

00:32:29.610 --> 00:32:33.450
about the prospect that
technology has for delivering

00:32:33.450 --> 00:32:37.310
us from an increasingly
unstable future,

00:32:37.310 --> 00:32:40.170
I believe it is our
responsibility as parents

00:32:40.170 --> 00:32:44.140
to do our best to raise
children who as adults meet

00:32:44.140 --> 00:32:47.390
the challenges of the
future with an open heart

00:32:47.390 --> 00:32:49.880
and a focused mind.

00:32:49.880 --> 00:32:52.560
It will be much easier
for them to do this

00:32:52.560 --> 00:32:55.180
and to attain this
level of clarity

00:32:55.180 --> 00:32:58.500
if they can listen to
their heart's calling.

00:32:58.500 --> 00:33:01.610
If they know what
their gifts are,

00:33:01.610 --> 00:33:05.080
and if they can trust the
expression of their highest

00:33:05.080 --> 00:33:09.700
potential, and know how
it will support them,

00:33:09.700 --> 00:33:12.470
not only themselves,
but those around them.

00:33:15.580 --> 00:33:19.200
So if you'd like to explore
these matters in more depth

00:33:19.200 --> 00:33:22.990
and gain more insight in how to
parent more consciously, please

00:33:22.990 --> 00:33:27.000
join us at the Sacred
Stream Center in Berkeley.

00:33:27.000 --> 00:33:29.800
Weekly classes are
starting March 2.

00:33:29.800 --> 00:33:32.960
And if you're interested in
our offering those classes

00:33:32.960 --> 00:33:36.500
in this context here to
the Google community,

00:33:36.500 --> 00:33:38.620
just let Ruchika know.

00:33:38.620 --> 00:33:43.030
But for now I ask you to
bring forward some questions.

00:33:43.030 --> 00:33:47.190
I love questions, even questions
on things we haven't covered,

00:33:47.190 --> 00:33:48.990
because there's so
much to parenting

00:33:48.990 --> 00:33:52.060
that it's hard to cover
it in a short talk.

00:33:52.060 --> 00:33:55.491
So please.

00:33:55.491 --> 00:33:56.490
Anybody have a question?

00:33:56.490 --> 00:33:57.580
You had a question, right?

00:33:57.580 --> 00:33:58.445
Ruchika, did you want
to say something?

00:33:58.445 --> 00:34:00.191
RUCHIKA: I'm going
to pass on the mic.

00:34:00.191 --> 00:34:01.145
ISA GUCCIARDI: Oh, OK.

00:34:01.145 --> 00:34:02.560
RUCHIKA: I put it under here.

00:34:02.560 --> 00:34:03.060
There it is.

00:34:03.060 --> 00:34:04.768
ISA GUCCIARDI: You
had a question, right?

00:34:04.768 --> 00:34:05.520
He had a question.

00:34:08.287 --> 00:34:09.370
AUDIENCE: Hi, I'm Phillip.

00:34:09.370 --> 00:34:11.480
Thanks for being here.

00:34:11.480 --> 00:34:14.489
My question is, the
things you talk about, do

00:34:14.489 --> 00:34:19.120
you have any data of how
much it actually matters,

00:34:19.120 --> 00:34:25.139
as in give child a good
environment to grow up in.

00:34:25.139 --> 00:34:28.310
But all these micromanagerial
type of things.

00:34:28.310 --> 00:34:29.370
Do they actually matter?

00:34:29.370 --> 00:34:34.409
Like if we obstruct the child's
expression of their talents,

00:34:34.409 --> 00:34:36.340
aren't they going
to end up actually

00:34:36.340 --> 00:34:38.250
doing what they want anyways?

00:34:38.250 --> 00:34:44.280
I mean, how much real direction
control do we have as parents?

00:34:44.280 --> 00:34:47.159
Like, this is all something
we might choose to do.

00:34:47.159 --> 00:34:51.654
But in retrospect,
does it really matter?

00:34:51.654 --> 00:34:53.320
ISA GUCCIARDI: Well,
you know, if you're

00:34:53.320 --> 00:34:56.590
going to speak at that
level, then you're saying,

00:34:56.590 --> 00:34:58.380
well, the child has
their own destiny.

00:34:58.380 --> 00:34:59.574
They have their own fate.

00:34:59.574 --> 00:35:01.990
It doesn't matter what we do
because they're following it.

00:35:01.990 --> 00:35:03.747
Is that what you're saying?

00:35:03.747 --> 00:35:05.330
AUDIENCE: I'm not a
proponent of fate.

00:35:05.330 --> 00:35:07.108
I'm just asking about the data.

00:35:11.420 --> 00:35:13.450
ISA GUCCIARDI: I think
that it's difficult

00:35:13.450 --> 00:35:17.900
when you're dealing with
issues of expression,

00:35:17.900 --> 00:35:20.470
of the ineffable.

00:35:20.470 --> 00:35:25.960
It's hard to have hard
data that supports

00:35:25.960 --> 00:35:35.680
or that denies the efficacy
or the authenticity

00:35:35.680 --> 00:35:38.510
of that expression,
because we are really far

00:35:38.510 --> 00:35:41.830
into the ineffable when
we think about what

00:35:41.830 --> 00:35:46.580
is it that impels us
into the world, what

00:35:46.580 --> 00:35:48.780
is it that draws us.

00:35:48.780 --> 00:35:55.530
And I spend most days
working with people

00:35:55.530 --> 00:35:59.390
who have been really badly
wounded in their childhood,

00:35:59.390 --> 00:36:03.990
where they've had-- I mean,
sometimes I joke around

00:36:03.990 --> 00:36:05.910
and I say, all you
have to do these days

00:36:05.910 --> 00:36:08.520
in order to be
wounded is be born.

00:36:08.520 --> 00:36:11.370
It's so hard to be in
the world right now.

00:36:11.370 --> 00:36:14.740
But one of the things
that I see again

00:36:14.740 --> 00:36:17.900
and again every day,
I mean 10 hours a day,

00:36:17.900 --> 00:36:23.130
is that people who have
been hurt or interrupted

00:36:23.130 --> 00:36:26.560
in being able to
rest in themselves

00:36:26.560 --> 00:36:29.610
have serious problems
later in life.

00:36:29.610 --> 00:36:34.002
And those problems can range
from anxiety, depression.

00:36:34.002 --> 00:36:36.210
I mean, look at the number
of people-- you want data?

00:36:36.210 --> 00:36:38.991
Look at the number of people
who are on antidepressants.

00:36:38.991 --> 00:36:39.490
What is it?

00:36:39.490 --> 00:36:41.700
Like 20 million?

00:36:41.700 --> 00:36:43.640
I mean, sometimes I'm
in a grocery store

00:36:43.640 --> 00:36:45.020
and I look around.

00:36:45.020 --> 00:36:47.470
And I realize I'm
the only person

00:36:47.470 --> 00:36:50.110
in this place that is
not altered-- either

00:36:50.110 --> 00:36:55.620
on prescription drugs or on
pot or on alcohol or on heroin

00:36:55.620 --> 00:36:56.670
or on ice.

00:36:56.670 --> 00:37:00.876
It's like, everybody is trying
to get away from themselves.

00:37:00.876 --> 00:37:03.250
And the reason they're trying
to get away from themselves

00:37:03.250 --> 00:37:06.390
is because they
weren't parented well.

00:37:06.390 --> 00:37:09.160
People who can
rest in themselves,

00:37:09.160 --> 00:37:12.180
people who know
themselves, people

00:37:12.180 --> 00:37:14.680
who understand what's
important for them

00:37:14.680 --> 00:37:18.320
and want to express that
importance and trust that they

00:37:18.320 --> 00:37:23.090
can express that importance,
don't need drugs.

00:37:23.090 --> 00:37:25.290
So I don't know if that
answers your question.

00:37:25.290 --> 00:37:28.076
But hopefully I got
somewhere near there.

00:37:28.076 --> 00:37:29.028
AUDIENCE: Thank you.

00:37:29.028 --> 00:37:29.980
ISA GUCCIARDI: Mm hm.

00:37:31.720 --> 00:37:33.680
AUDIENCE: As I've
been trying to become

00:37:33.680 --> 00:37:36.130
more mindful in my
own practice and not

00:37:36.130 --> 00:37:39.177
trigger as quickly, you know,
be more detached and everything.

00:37:39.177 --> 00:37:41.260
One of the places I've
found it hardest to do that

00:37:41.260 --> 00:37:42.595
is in parenting.

00:37:42.595 --> 00:37:44.470
I have an almost
five-year-old girl and a one

00:37:44.470 --> 00:37:45.190
and one half-year-old boy.

00:37:45.190 --> 00:37:46.606
And one of the
things I've noticed

00:37:46.606 --> 00:37:48.710
is obviously kids
trigger you a lot.

00:37:48.710 --> 00:37:49.220
Right?

00:37:49.220 --> 00:37:50.761
They're sort of
almost programmed to.

00:37:50.761 --> 00:37:53.630
But I've also found I try
to sometimes be detached

00:37:53.630 --> 00:37:54.967
and say, let's do this thing.

00:37:54.967 --> 00:37:55.800
Let's do this thing.

00:37:55.800 --> 00:37:58.160
But oftentimes being a little
bit more forceful in terms

00:37:58.160 --> 00:38:00.368
of getting a little bit
angry or showing a little bit

00:38:00.368 --> 00:38:03.490
of disappointment or even
being a little bit stronger,

00:38:03.490 --> 00:38:05.680
it compels them in a way
then just sort of saying,

00:38:05.680 --> 00:38:07.860
let's not make a mess, let's
not make a mess over and over

00:38:07.860 --> 00:38:08.190
doesn't.

00:38:08.190 --> 00:38:10.356
And so I struggle with that
because on the one hand,

00:38:10.356 --> 00:38:13.694
I don't want to just be reacting
from my amygdala to my kids.

00:38:13.694 --> 00:38:15.360
I want to be compassionate
and so forth.

00:38:15.360 --> 00:38:18.980
But kids often do seem to
respond more to a little bit

00:38:18.980 --> 00:38:20.530
more forceful response.

00:38:20.530 --> 00:38:24.040
I'm just curious how you think
about resolving that paradox.

00:38:24.040 --> 00:38:27.570
How to remain mindful, but still
be compelling to your kids.

00:38:27.570 --> 00:38:29.070
ISA GUCCIARDI: I
don't think there's

00:38:29.070 --> 00:38:30.700
any contradiction
between mindfulness

00:38:30.700 --> 00:38:32.490
and being compelling.

00:38:32.490 --> 00:38:35.690
I think that this is
important for your children

00:38:35.690 --> 00:38:38.110
to understand that
there are structures.

00:38:38.110 --> 00:38:42.900
And you play a little bit.

00:38:42.900 --> 00:38:45.070
OK, let's put it all away.

00:38:45.070 --> 00:38:46.010
Here we are.

00:38:46.010 --> 00:38:46.980
Sing a song.

00:38:46.980 --> 00:38:47.924
Put it away.

00:38:47.924 --> 00:38:49.590
And then they start
punching each other.

00:38:49.590 --> 00:38:51.320
It's like, OK.

00:38:51.320 --> 00:38:52.570
We're not playing anymore.

00:38:52.570 --> 00:38:54.020
We're putting things away.

00:38:54.020 --> 00:38:58.410
And you can have that
kind of compelling quality

00:38:58.410 --> 00:38:59.410
in your voice.

00:38:59.410 --> 00:39:01.410
But you need to
strip out the anger.

00:39:01.410 --> 00:39:03.940
And that's what the mindfulness
practice helps with.

00:39:03.940 --> 00:39:09.770
But I don't think it's a problem
giving very clear, compelling

00:39:09.770 --> 00:39:11.352
statements to your children.

00:39:11.352 --> 00:39:12.310
I think it's important.

00:39:12.310 --> 00:39:13.130
They need that.

00:39:13.130 --> 00:39:15.410
AUDIENCE: If you're firm,
even in a detached way,

00:39:15.410 --> 00:39:17.819
that works as well as--

00:39:17.819 --> 00:39:19.110
ISA GUCCIARDI: It works better.

00:39:19.110 --> 00:39:21.540
It works better.

00:39:21.540 --> 00:39:23.446
If you've got anger
issues coming up,

00:39:23.446 --> 00:39:24.820
it probably doesn't
have anything

00:39:24.820 --> 00:39:27.740
to do with the child
doing what they're doing.

00:39:27.740 --> 00:39:30.050
So one of the great
things about parenting

00:39:30.050 --> 00:39:33.800
is that it's a workshop to show
you the places within yourself

00:39:33.800 --> 00:39:35.670
that you haven't addressed yet.

00:39:35.670 --> 00:39:38.045
And that's why you're saying
like they kind of go for it.

00:39:38.045 --> 00:39:40.300
They do kind of go for it.

00:39:40.300 --> 00:39:41.060
They want to push.

00:39:41.060 --> 00:39:44.130
They want to know how big
a container do I have here?

00:39:44.130 --> 00:39:47.310
You know, how much can I
trust you to support me

00:39:47.310 --> 00:39:49.760
without getting off balance?

00:39:49.760 --> 00:39:52.670
And what happens
when I push you?

00:39:52.670 --> 00:39:55.330
I mean, those are important
questions for children

00:39:55.330 --> 00:39:57.060
to know the answer to.

00:39:57.060 --> 00:39:59.070
And what's really
important to do

00:39:59.070 --> 00:40:02.360
is to give them a clear answer.

00:40:02.360 --> 00:40:04.340
You can push me this far.

00:40:04.340 --> 00:40:06.240
But you can't push
me any further.

00:40:06.240 --> 00:40:09.110
And if you push me any further,
I'm not going to get angry.

00:40:09.110 --> 00:40:10.760
I'm not going to reject you.

00:40:10.760 --> 00:40:12.909
But you are going to
have some consequences.

00:40:12.909 --> 00:40:14.700
And we're going to
apply those consequences

00:40:14.700 --> 00:40:17.560
in a consistent and clear way.

00:40:17.560 --> 00:40:19.736
And I think that--

00:40:19.736 --> 00:40:20.450
AUDIENCE: And that's the
structure you're talking about.

00:40:20.450 --> 00:40:21.560
ISA GUCCIARDI: That's the
structure we're talking about.

00:40:21.560 --> 00:40:22.710
Exactly.

00:40:22.710 --> 00:40:25.690
And you know, if you
address your anger issues,

00:40:25.690 --> 00:40:26.880
then you've got a structure.

00:40:26.880 --> 00:40:28.350
If you don't address
your anger issues,

00:40:28.350 --> 00:40:29.490
you don't have a structure.

00:40:29.490 --> 00:40:33.110
Or the kids are like, I
don't know what to do.

00:40:33.110 --> 00:40:34.310
And then they pull back.

00:40:34.310 --> 00:40:37.330
They hold back.

00:40:37.330 --> 00:40:40.210
They're thinking about
what am I going to do

00:40:40.210 --> 00:40:41.970
and how is it going
to affect you,

00:40:41.970 --> 00:40:43.770
rather than what
am I going to do

00:40:43.770 --> 00:40:46.000
and how is that
going to affect me.

00:40:46.000 --> 00:40:48.210
You don't want to have
children in that position.

00:40:48.210 --> 00:40:49.390
They want to know.

00:40:49.390 --> 00:40:52.850
They need to know what's going
to happen at any given time,

00:40:52.850 --> 00:40:53.590
in general.

00:40:53.590 --> 00:40:55.680
I mean, of course,
things can happen

00:40:55.680 --> 00:40:57.240
that are outside the box.

00:40:57.240 --> 00:41:01.177
But they generally need
to have consistency.

00:41:01.177 --> 00:41:02.760
And I think it's a
big mistake-- a lot

00:41:02.760 --> 00:41:04.190
of times in
spiritual communities

00:41:04.190 --> 00:41:06.600
there's this idea that you're
not allowed to be angry,

00:41:06.600 --> 00:41:08.391
or that you shouldn't
listen to your anger,

00:41:08.391 --> 00:41:10.480
or you should
overcome your anger.

00:41:10.480 --> 00:41:13.520
I actually think anger
tells us important things.

00:41:13.520 --> 00:41:17.910
And I think that you can't just
be unleashing your anger all

00:41:17.910 --> 00:41:20.490
the time and say, oh, I
have my right to my anger.

00:41:20.490 --> 00:41:24.120
But if you are
getting angry, it may

00:41:24.120 --> 00:41:27.290
be because your
boundary's being violated.

00:41:27.290 --> 00:41:28.910
Or your child may
be getting angry

00:41:28.910 --> 00:41:30.956
because her boundaries
are being violated.

00:41:30.956 --> 00:41:32.330
And that needs to
be listened to.

00:41:32.330 --> 00:41:34.872
And you don't want to give
her the same instruction

00:41:34.872 --> 00:41:35.830
that you give yourself.

00:41:35.830 --> 00:41:36.996
I have to overcome my anger.

00:41:36.996 --> 00:41:38.680
I can't be angry.

00:41:38.680 --> 00:41:42.670
And she's got somebody who's
taking her books at school all

00:41:42.670 --> 00:41:43.170
the time.

00:41:43.170 --> 00:41:44.010
And she's angry.

00:41:44.010 --> 00:41:44.510
Good.

00:41:44.510 --> 00:41:45.380
She should be angry.

00:41:45.380 --> 00:41:46.600
Right?

00:41:46.600 --> 00:41:47.610
It's not like, OK.

00:41:47.610 --> 00:41:49.100
Let's think about forgiveness.

00:41:49.100 --> 00:41:49.870
No.

00:41:49.870 --> 00:41:51.980
Let's think about
why are you angry.

00:41:51.980 --> 00:41:53.840
You're angry because
you're being violated.

00:41:53.840 --> 00:41:55.630
How are you being violated?

00:41:55.630 --> 00:41:57.240
How do you deal
with that violation?

00:41:57.240 --> 00:42:00.470
What is the most useful
way in approaching,

00:42:00.470 --> 00:42:03.700
working with that violation,
other than your anger?

00:42:03.700 --> 00:42:05.200
But listen to the anger.

00:42:05.200 --> 00:42:05.700
Right?

00:42:05.700 --> 00:42:08.402
So I could give that
same advice to you.

00:42:08.402 --> 00:42:09.290
AUDIENCE: Thank you.

00:42:19.290 --> 00:42:20.570
AUDIENCE: Thank you.

00:42:20.570 --> 00:42:23.120
How useful would it
be if in addition

00:42:23.120 --> 00:42:26.610
to listening to their
child's calling and interests

00:42:26.610 --> 00:42:28.250
and providing that
environment for them

00:42:28.250 --> 00:42:30.400
to fulfill that
potential, you also

00:42:30.400 --> 00:42:34.870
introduce a more structured
mindfulness practice.

00:42:34.870 --> 00:42:36.870
Some sort of practice
in which they

00:42:36.870 --> 00:42:39.690
are asked to sit and to breathe
and do something that clearly

00:42:39.690 --> 00:42:41.620
is not coming from
them, but rather

00:42:41.620 --> 00:42:44.500
from us trying to teach them
some tools and skills that

00:42:44.500 --> 00:42:46.580
are useful for us.

00:42:46.580 --> 00:42:49.620
Is that going against that
principle law of allowing

00:42:49.620 --> 00:42:51.180
them to be themselves?

00:42:51.180 --> 00:42:51.930
ISA GUCCIARDI: No.

00:42:51.930 --> 00:42:53.850
The idea of doing some
kind of a structure

00:42:53.850 --> 00:42:57.730
liked a mindfulness practice is
exactly what I'm talking about.

00:42:57.730 --> 00:43:01.610
It's a structure that's coming
out of the set of values

00:43:01.610 --> 00:43:03.140
that you hold dear.

00:43:03.140 --> 00:43:04.180
OK?

00:43:04.180 --> 00:43:07.132
So you're going to sit with
your child and say, OK.

00:43:07.132 --> 00:43:08.840
This is something
that's important to me.

00:43:08.840 --> 00:43:10.850
This is something that I value.

00:43:10.850 --> 00:43:16.560
And I'd like to offer it to
you to see what you do with it.

00:43:16.560 --> 00:43:20.210
And you know, I don't think that
that's inhibiting the child's

00:43:20.210 --> 00:43:22.490
expression in any way.

00:43:22.490 --> 00:43:24.520
It's offering, again,
structures that

00:43:24.520 --> 00:43:27.630
are based on your values
through which the child can

00:43:27.630 --> 00:43:29.259
learn about themselves.

00:43:29.259 --> 00:43:30.050
And that's helpful.

00:43:33.110 --> 00:43:34.485
AUDIENCE: Thank
you for the talk.

00:43:34.485 --> 00:43:39.340
I was wondering about the
idea of the deepest calling.

00:43:39.340 --> 00:43:42.840
And to what extent do
you think it's something

00:43:42.840 --> 00:43:44.920
that's kind of set at birth?

00:43:44.920 --> 00:43:47.530
And to what extent do you
think it might be influenced

00:43:47.530 --> 00:43:51.740
by the experiences the child
has maybe before he or she is

00:43:51.740 --> 00:43:56.626
able to demonstrate affinity for
any particular sort of thing?

00:43:56.626 --> 00:43:57.500
ISA GUCCIARDI: Sorry.

00:43:57.500 --> 00:43:58.090
What?

00:43:58.090 --> 00:44:00.971
AUDIENCE: Maybe like
um-- to what extent

00:44:00.971 --> 00:44:02.720
do you think that that
might be influenced

00:44:02.720 --> 00:44:06.910
by the experiences the child has
before he or she is old enough

00:44:06.910 --> 00:44:11.280
to be able to show an affinity
for certain types of things

00:44:11.280 --> 00:44:13.330
or people or experiences?

00:44:13.330 --> 00:44:15.970
I guess part of my question
is how young do you

00:44:15.970 --> 00:44:18.670
see this calling in children?

00:44:18.670 --> 00:44:21.560
ISA GUCCIARDI: I see It from
almost the moment they're born.

00:44:21.560 --> 00:44:22.060
Yeah.

00:44:22.060 --> 00:44:26.172
And there are lots
of experiences

00:44:26.172 --> 00:44:27.130
that children can have.

00:44:27.130 --> 00:44:29.710
You're asking, is this is
something that's in them?

00:44:29.710 --> 00:44:31.840
Or is it something
that comes forward

00:44:31.840 --> 00:44:37.570
as they mature and have external
environmental influences

00:44:37.570 --> 00:44:39.820
on them?

00:44:39.820 --> 00:44:45.530
The question of nature
versus nurture, right?

00:44:45.530 --> 00:44:47.420
Again, so here's my opinion, OK.

00:44:47.420 --> 00:44:51.690
So I actually firmly,
totally, and completely

00:44:51.690 --> 00:44:56.260
believe-- OK,
there's an opinion--

00:44:56.260 --> 00:45:03.760
that everyone has something in
them that calls them to life.

00:45:03.760 --> 00:45:07.920
And different people have
different experiences

00:45:07.920 --> 00:45:13.220
that either help them
fulfill that calling,

00:45:13.220 --> 00:45:16.520
or they have experiences
where their experience of life

00:45:16.520 --> 00:45:18.625
is a thwarting of that calling.

00:45:18.625 --> 00:45:22.020
But the calling is
there either way.

00:45:22.020 --> 00:45:23.184
And it depends.

00:45:23.184 --> 00:45:24.600
I mean, one of the
great tragedies

00:45:24.600 --> 00:45:28.630
that I see every day is how
many people have so much beauty

00:45:28.630 --> 00:45:32.310
in them that they can't express
because of their wounding

00:45:32.310 --> 00:45:34.090
or their pain, right?

