00:49:57.560 --> 00:49:59.990
need to do to keep them safe?

00:49:59.990 --> 00:50:02.050
And what do I need to
do to keep them happy?

00:50:04.700 --> 00:50:07.710
And that doesn't mean giving
them all the candy they want.

00:50:07.710 --> 00:50:10.375
It doesn't mean putting
them on a leash.

00:50:14.190 --> 00:50:17.800
So especially when
they're little,

00:50:17.800 --> 00:50:21.050
those are two things that you
can always focus on if you're

00:50:21.050 --> 00:50:23.150
trying to make a decision.

00:50:23.150 --> 00:50:25.810
What do I think about
this computer game?

00:50:25.810 --> 00:50:26.960
OK.

00:50:26.960 --> 00:50:29.650
Is this going to keep
my kid feeling safe?

00:50:29.650 --> 00:50:32.290
Or is the violence in that game
going to give them nightmares?

00:50:32.290 --> 00:50:32.720
OK.

00:50:32.720 --> 00:50:35.261
I guess I'm not going to give
them that computer game, right?

00:50:37.930 --> 00:50:41.810
But if you think about safety
and happiness, and then

00:50:41.810 --> 00:50:44.410
you just use that as a measure
as you're holding it up

00:50:44.410 --> 00:50:47.325
against all of the
bombardment, as you say,

00:50:47.325 --> 00:50:49.630
of the cultural environment.

00:50:49.630 --> 00:50:53.510
I have to say as a parent, I
felt like my main primary duty

00:50:53.510 --> 00:50:56.022
became filtering the culture.

00:50:56.022 --> 00:50:58.480
It was so important because
there's so much in the culture.

00:50:58.480 --> 00:51:00.521
I mean, I have a degree
in cultural anthropology.

00:51:00.521 --> 00:51:03.400
So I'm already looking
at culture, right?

00:51:03.400 --> 00:51:09.570
But there's so much in the
culture that is deadening.

00:51:09.570 --> 00:51:12.270
And you have to decide--
again, that's my opinion.

00:51:12.270 --> 00:51:14.320
Right?

00:51:14.320 --> 00:51:16.390
And you have to
decide, to what extent

00:51:16.390 --> 00:51:20.850
do I want my child to
be influenced by that?

00:51:20.850 --> 00:51:22.760
And the way you answer
that is, is this

00:51:22.760 --> 00:51:25.650
going to keep my
child happy and safe?

00:51:25.650 --> 00:51:26.240
Right?

00:51:26.240 --> 00:51:30.290
I find that that is a really--
if you don't take anything

00:51:30.290 --> 00:51:33.590
else away from this
talk-- just think, mantra.

00:51:33.590 --> 00:51:35.906
What will keep my
child happy and safe?

00:51:35.906 --> 00:51:38.030
And you may have different
ideas than other people.

00:51:38.030 --> 00:51:40.300
But you know you're
doing your best.

00:51:40.300 --> 00:51:42.790
Again, I don't think
there's one answer.

00:51:42.790 --> 00:51:46.260
Because I think there
are general answers.

00:51:46.260 --> 00:51:50.100
But every child has
their own tolerances.

00:51:50.100 --> 00:51:52.670
And every parent has
their own set of values.

00:51:52.670 --> 00:51:55.600
So again, you have to
have enough structure

00:51:55.600 --> 00:51:57.950
to allow for a
range of expression,

00:51:57.950 --> 00:52:00.330
not so much structure
that you crush it.

00:52:00.330 --> 00:52:04.180
And those two questions--
what will keep my child safe.

00:52:04.180 --> 00:52:06.710
And what will keep
my child happy.

00:52:06.710 --> 00:52:09.270
Navigate those two
poles pretty well.

00:52:09.270 --> 00:52:11.188
Hopefully that's helpful.

