we're older to confront it.

00:54:04.590 --> 00:54:10.760
But I think that
also there is a lot

00:54:10.760 --> 00:54:13.560
of violence in this culture.

00:54:13.560 --> 00:54:16.190
I know that's my opinion.

00:54:16.190 --> 00:54:19.120
But there is a lot of
violence in this culture.

00:54:19.120 --> 00:54:21.520
And when you have
a lot of violence

00:54:21.520 --> 00:54:24.460
that is tolerated,
like on TV shows

00:54:24.460 --> 00:54:27.190
and cartoons and
video games, when

00:54:27.190 --> 00:54:30.420
you have a lot of violence
that is witnessed and seen

00:54:30.420 --> 00:54:33.350
in all the different media
places where children are

00:54:33.350 --> 00:54:36.770
seeing it, it's
not too far a step

00:54:36.770 --> 00:54:40.540
to think about that violence
being turned inward.

00:54:40.540 --> 00:54:45.450
It's like there's a tolerance
of violence in the culture

00:54:45.450 --> 00:54:49.000
generally that I personally
think is not healthy.

00:54:49.000 --> 00:54:52.160
So the idea of
self-destruction is not

00:54:52.160 --> 00:54:54.820
too far away from the
kind of destruction

00:54:54.820 --> 00:54:56.870
that they're seeing all
around them all the time.

00:54:56.870 --> 00:54:58.650
Now, I think that every
one of those children--

00:54:58.650 --> 00:55:00.150
like I would really
like to sit down

00:55:00.150 --> 00:55:02.030
with every one of
